00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:53,030
Yes, I am.

14
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:55,930
Do you know Bong-pal?
Park Bong-pal.

15
00:01:56,530 --> 00:01:58,259
- Yes.
- Ah.

16
00:01:58,330 --> 00:02:01,760
I'm like an uncle to him.

17
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:06,160
I heard his professor worked here
so I stopped by to say hello.

18
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:09,759
Is that right?
It's nice to meet you.

19
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:18,600
You seem very familiar.
Have we ever met before?

20
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:25,100
Come to think of it, I think we saw
each other around the neighborhood.

21
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,730
No.

22
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,860
It was a very long time ago.

23
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:43,329
I'm not sure.

24
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:46,760
- I don't remember.
- I see.

25
00:02:51,530 --> 00:02:53,400
Hello.

26
00:02:54,329 --> 00:02:57,030
- We got lunch.
- Go ahead and eat first.

27
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:03,700
I see it's lunchtime. Forgive me
for taking so much of your time.

28
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:06,630
- Not at all.
- Please enjoy your lunch.

29
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:09,130
Please, take good care
of my Bong-pal.

30
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,660
I will.

31
00:03:26,230 --> 00:03:28,260
Excuse me then.

32
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,160
Oh, sir.

33
00:03:36,829 --> 00:03:39,660
- I'll see you around.
- Yes.

34
